Interface GroupingFilter<T>

  • Type Parameters:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GroupingFilter.Equal, GroupingFilter.False, GroupingFilter.GreaterThan, GroupingFilter.GreaterThanEqual, GroupingFilter.LessThan, GroupingFilter.LessThanEqual, GroupingFilter.RangeImpl, GroupingFilter.True
    public interface GroupingFilter<T>
extends java.util.function.Predicate<T>
    A grouping filter is a type of Predicate that may be combined with other instances. The combination of two GroupingFilter objects results in a GroupingFilter that selects values that satisfy both of the functions in a single operations. This is useful because we can describe work to do in terms of fewer functions.
